Recipe is from Jenny our Development Director.INGREDIENTS:2 lemons1 medium onion chopped1 large bell pepper chopped1 cup of chopped celery1 1/2 cups cooked or 1 (15.5-ounce) BPA-free can or Tetra Pak salt-free kidney beans drained and rinsed1 teaspoon garlic powder1 teaspoon dried thyme1 teaspoon dried oregano1/2 teaspoon paprika1/4-1/2 teaspoon black pepper1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder1/4 teaspoon cayenne1/4- 1/2 cup of no-salt added vegetable broth or water*Cooked quinoa to serveMETHOD:1. Heat the juice of two lemons in a pot over medium heat and sauté the chopped onion bell pepper and celery.2. Once the veggies are soft add in the kidney beans spices and vegetable broth. Stir everything together and simmer for a few minutes. Cook until the dish is heated thoroughly.3. Serve with the cooked quinoa and enjoy!Makes enough for about 3-4 people*The Light Vegetable Broth from the How Not to Diet Cookbook is here: https://nutritionfacts.org/recipe/light-vegetable-broth/#HowNotToDie #DailyDozen #EatMorePlants #LifestyleMedicine #DailyDozenMeals #plantbasedrecipes #EatYourBeans #QuinoaRecipes #WholeGrains #KidneyBeans #PlantPowered #FruitsAndVeggies #EatYourVeggies
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "nutrition_facts_org"  "comment_text": "Here is a simple and delicious Daily Dozen inspired meal to make this weekend: Red Beans and Quinoa. Recipe is from Jenny  our Development Director.

INGREDIENTS:
2 lemons
1 medium onion  chopped
1 large bell pepper  chopped
1 cup of chopped celery
1 1/2 cups cooked or 1 (15.5-ounce) BPA-free can or Tetra Pak salt-free kidney beans  drained and rinsed
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried oregano
1/2 teaspoon paprika
1/4-1/2 teaspoon black pepper
1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder
1/4 teaspoon cayenne
1/4- 1/2 cup of no-salt added vegetable broth or water*
Cooked quinoa  to serve

METHOD:
1. Heat the juice of two lemons in a pot over medium heat and sauté the chopped onion  bell pepper  and celery.
2. Once the veggies are soft  add in the kidney beans  spices  and vegetable broth. Stir everything together and simmer for a few minutes. Cook until the dish is heated thoroughly.
3. Serve with the cooked quinoa and enjoy!
Makes enough for about 3-4 people

*The Light Vegetable Broth from the How Not to Diet Cookbook is here: https://nutritionfacts.org/recipe/light-vegetable-broth/

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mfoodbym"  "comment_text": "• C H I L I  C O N  C A R N E  W R A P S •

❓Schon mal Chili con Carne Wraps ausprobiert?😍🌯

Rezept (1 großer Wrap ~30cm oder 2 kleine)

| 570 kcal | 14g Fett | 67g Kohlh | 41g Eiw |

▪️1 Wrap (bei mir 85g)
▪️1 Zwiebel
▪️1 Knoblauchzehe
▪️100g fettreduziertes Rinderhackfleisch (oder Alternative)
▪️100g gehackte Dosentomaten + nach Bedarf Wasser
▪️65g Kidneybohnen
▪️60g Mais
▪️Gewürze

▪️evtl. körniger Frischkäse
▪️evtl. Salat

STEP 1 - Chili zubereiten
Zwiebeln und Knoblauch anbraten und das Hackfleisch oder eine Alternative hinzufügen. Dies löscht du dann mit den Tomaten ab und lässt diese Masse dann einige Minuten köcheln  bevor die Kidneybohnen sowie Mais untergerührt werden. Zuletzt noch würzen und so lange köcheln  bis du die gewünschte Konsistenz erreicht hast bzw. Wasser hinzufügen.

STEP 3 - Wraps Rollen
Bestreiche die Wraps nach Bedarf mit dem Frischkäse und belege ihn mit Salat. Anschließend das Chili con Carne darauf verteilen und den Wrap aufrollen.

🔝Speichert euch den Beitrag ab und berichtet mir gerne von eurem Ergebnis 📷

main_text: Lectins can do WHAT ⁉️Lectins are stable in an acidic environment which is why they don’t get broken down by our stomach enzymes 🦠 They then enter our small intestine and then the bloodstrea🩸 Lectins have been cited as the cause of 👇🏼🥔 Some autoimmune diseases🥜 Chronic inflammation🌽 ObesityPeople can be so sensitive that even a small amount will cause a reaction. For example raw and/or uncooked kidney bean in the smallest amount have been known to cause severe nausea vomiting and diarrhea because of “phytohemagglutinin” which is a type of lectin that binds to red blood cells once it passes into the bloodstream.If you are experiencing symptoms like diarrhea nausea fatigue or vomiting it’s best to be aware of the foods that have a high lectin content and treat it.The most common treatment is a lectin-avoidance diet. Luckily diets such as keto paleo and low-carb that are based on whole foods can EASILY be tailored to avoid lectins. 🚫Do you currently avoid these high lectin foods? How has it helped your overall feeling after eating? comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "shawnwells"  "comment_text": "Lectins can do WHAT ⁉️

Lectins are stable in an acidic environment which is why they don’t get broken down by our stomach enzymes 🦠 They then enter our small intestine  and then the bloodstrea🩸 

Lectins have been cited as the cause of 👇🏼

🥔 Some autoimmune diseases
🥜 Chronic inflammation
🌽 Obesity

People can be so sensitive that even a small amount will cause a reaction. For example  raw and/or uncooked kidney bean  in the smallest amount  have been known to cause severe nausea  vomiting and diarrhea because of “phytohemagglutinin”  which is a type of lectin that binds to red blood cells once it passes into the bloodstream.

If you are experiencing symptoms like diarrhea  nausea  fatigue  or vomiting it’s best to be aware of the foods that have a high lectin content and treat it.

The most common treatment is a lectin-avoidance diet. Luckily  diets such as keto  paleo  and low-carb  that are based on whole foods can EASILY be tailored to avoid lectins. 🚫

main_text: Hvor mange livretter kan man egentlig ha’?Jeg har ret mange. Men livretter er vel også lidt som musik. Nogle retter har man bare en anden kærlighed til fordi den minder en om en særlig tid.Chili con carne minder mig om min tid i vestjylland. Mit første job som udlært kok i 2005. På restauranten blev det lidt af en personale spise den sommer. Nat mad faktisk. Chili C. C. Skyllet ned med en kold fadøl efter sådan en 12 timers vagt med fuld skrald på.Nogle gange ønsker jeg mig tilbage til den tid. Andre gange er jeg taknemmelig for mit “8 til 4” job. Heldigvis formår vi at hælde lidt restaurations branche stemning ind i køkkenet flere gange dagligt. Altså på den gode måde.Selvom ingen af os før har arbejdet sammen så har vi alligevel så meget tilfælles når vi taler om “gamle” dage. Det er så fedt. Vi har det i blodet jeg elsker det.Og idag har været en helt særlig dag! Første dag med fuldt hold. HOLDET!- byens hold - vores hold - mit hold. Tak for jer. Det bliver så pisse godt. Fraaaaaaa nu af 💪🏽👊🏽🙌🏽.👩🏽‍🍳📸: @aranjanieriksen#dagensret #chiliconcarne #chilisincarne #chilicc #frokost #personalerestaurant #viholderafhverdagen #meyerskantiner #bønner #kidneybeans #sortebønner #bælgfrugter #smag #kærlighed #passion #cheflife #mylife #spisesalen42 #frederiksplads #frederiksbjerg #aarhus
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "food_vaerksted"  "comment_text": "Hvor mange livretter kan man egentlig ha’?
Jeg har ret mange. Men livretter er vel også lidt som musik. Nogle retter har man bare en anden kærlighed til fordi den minder en om en særlig tid.

Chili con carne minder mig om min tid i vestjylland. Mit første job som udlært kok i 2005. På restauranten blev det lidt af en personale spise den sommer. Nat mad faktisk. Chili C. C. Skyllet ned med en kold fadøl efter sådan en 12 timers vagt med fuld skrald på.

Nogle gange ønsker jeg mig tilbage til den tid. Andre gange er jeg taknemmelig for mit “8 til 4” job. Heldigvis formår vi at hælde lidt restaurations branche stemning ind i køkkenet flere gange dagligt. Altså på den gode måde.

Selvom ingen af os før har arbejdet sammen  så har vi alligevel så meget tilfælles når vi taler om “gamle” dage. Det er så fedt. Vi har det i blodet  jeg elsker det.

Og idag har været en helt særlig dag! Første dag med fuldt hold. HOLDET!
- byens hold - vores hold - mit hold. Tak for jer. Det bliver så pisse godt. Fraaaaaaa nu af 💪🏽👊🏽🙌🏽.

main_text: Mexican RiceIt is sure to liven up your day. It is zesty & flavorful vegan dish. We all love fried rice but I realized it was time to change it up with this restaurant style Mexican rice. This rice comes together so easily & quickly in a single pot which makes for an easy clean-up. This Mexican rice features hearty long-grained rice sauted with tomato purry & lots of veggies kidney beans & spices.Process1. First rinse 1 cup of long grained rice under cold running water a few times . This gets the starches out so that the rice doesn’t become sticky or mushy when stir fried.2. Next over medium heat pan add tbsp oil butter then add tomato purry spices chilli flakes & oregano then add ketchup in it & boil on high flame.3. Then add salsa sauce (In a mixer add little bit tomatoes jalapennos coriandersaltlemon grind it in semi-liquid form)4. Now add veggies like bell pepper capsicum sweet corn olives jalapennos & lastly qdd boiled kidney beans.5. Now add the drained rice to the hot pan. Mix well & stir continously as you saute the rice on the low heat. The putside of tge rice should start to het slightly beowned & lightly toasted but be careful that they do not burn.6. Now add 2 cups of vegetable stock/hot water depending on the quality of of ricr you are using mix well. Cover & cook the rice on a low heat for about 20-22 mins or untill tye rice grains qre tender  fluffy & all the liquids have been absorbed.7. Serve the Mexican rice hot in plate then add salsa sauce on top of it pieces of tortilla chips cheess then again repeat same steps.8. Garnish it with some olivesjalapennosbasil leavesFollow: @mishthefoodicon#mexicanrice #ricesidedish #eathealthy #instafood #veggies #kidneybeans #foodie #eatathome #foodiesinternationalchat #mexicanfood #foodiesofinstagram #mexicanmeals #explorepage #mexicanhealthyfood #thins2doinmumbai #trellingmumbai #mexicanfoodlovers #foodphotography #foodblogger
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mishthefoodicon"  "comment_text": "Mexican Rice
It is sure to liven up your day. It is zesty & flavorful vegan dish. We all love fried rice  but I realized it was time to change it up with this restaurant style Mexican rice. This rice comes together so easily & quickly in a single pot  which makes for an easy clean-up. This Mexican rice features hearty long-grained rice  sauted with tomato purry & lots of veggies  kidney beans & spices.

Process
1. First rinse 1 cup of long grained rice under cold running water a few times . This gets the starches out so that the rice doesn’t become sticky or mushy when stir fried.
2. Next over  medium heat pan add tbsp oil  butter then add tomato purry  spices  chilli flakes & oregano then add ketchup in it & boil on high flame.
3. Then add salsa sauce (In a mixer add little bit tomatoes  jalapennos  coriander salt lemon grind it in semi-liquid form)
4. Now add veggies like bell pepper  capsicum  sweet corn  olives  jalapennos & lastly qdd boiled kidney beans.
5. Now add the drained rice to the hot pan. Mix well & stir continously as you saute the rice on the low heat. The putside of tge rice should start to het slightly beowned & lightly toasted  but be careful that they do not burn.
6. Now add 2 cups of vegetable stock/hot water depending on the quality of of ricr you are using  mix well. Cover & cook the rice on a low heat for about 20-22 mins or untill tye rice grains qre tender   fluffy & all the liquids have been absorbed.
7. Serve the Mexican rice hot in plate then add salsa sauce on top of it  pieces of tortilla chips  cheess then again repeat same steps.
8. Garnish it with some olives jalapennos basil leaves

Follow: @mishthefoodicon

main_text: 🍔 Follow @greenveganclub for more! Full recipe by @luckiesgouin⁣Ingredients:- 1 white potato⁣- 1/3 cup quinoa (raw)⁣- 1 can of kidney beans⁣- 1 tsp paprika⁣- 1 tsp cumin⁣- Salt and pepper to taste⁣⁣Method:⁣1. Roast the potato with spices and then peel once it cools down. ⁣⁣2. Add the beans to the potato and mash it with a fork!⁣⁣3. Cook the quinoa and then add it to the mashed potatoes and beans. Mix well!⁣⁣4. With wet hands shape into burger patties and bake for 25 minutes at 450° F on a lined baking tray. ⁣⁣And basically that's it! Enjoy!⁣⁣---------------⁣#veganburgers #kidneybeans #cumin #veganlunchideas #quinoarecipes #plantbasedprotein #plantbasediet #plantbasemeal #healthyrecipies

Ingredients:
- 1 white potato⁣
- 1/3 cup quinoa (raw)⁣
- 1 can of kidney beans⁣
- 1 tsp paprika⁣
- 1 tsp cumin⁣
- Salt and pepper to taste⁣
⁣
Method:
⁣1. Roast the potato with spices and then peel once it cools down. ⁣
⁣2. Add the beans to the potato and mash it with a fork!⁣
⁣3. Cook the quinoa and then add it to the mashed potatoes and beans. Mix well!⁣
⁣4. With wet hands  shape into burger patties and bake for 25 minutes at 450° F on a lined baking tray. ⁣
⁣And basically  that's it! Enjoy!⁣
⁣---------------
⁣#veganburgers #kidneybeans #cumin #veganlunchideas #quinoarecipes #plantbasedprotein #plantbasediet #plantbasemeal #healthyrecipies"}}

main_text: Rajma-Chawal! 🍛/** Rajma-Chawal recipe **/Disclaimer: This is my version of Rajma as this is what suits my taste buds light on the tummy and easy on spices. Please feel free to add/modify ingredients based on your preferences.1. In a pressure cooker add 1 slit green chilli along with 5 chopped garlic pods and sauté for a few seconds.2.Add 1 large onion finely chopped and sauté until golden brown.3.Add 2 medium-sized tomatoes and let soften.4.Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell goes off.5.Now turn your flame low and add spices such as 1 tbspn kashmiri chilli powder 1 tspn turmeric powder 1 tbspn dhaniya-Zeera powder 1 tspn garam masala powder 1.5 tspn chaat masala and salt according to taste.6.After bhunofying these masalas along with the onion-tomatoes on a low flame add the Rajma(soaked overnight) and mix well.7.At this point also add finely chopped coriander and a dash of lime juice approx 1 tbspn.8.Add water just enough to soak the Rajma not too much not too little.9.Pressure cook for 4 whistles or until soft but not mushy.10.Let cool and eventually garnish with more finely chopped coriander.11.Goes well with both rice and chapati.#lunchspecial #rajma #rajmachawal #chawal #kidneybeans #redkidneybeans #steamedrice
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "lubnasfoodgram"  "comment_text": "Rajma-Chawal! 🍛

/** Rajma-Chawal recipe **/

Disclaimer: This is my version of Rajma as this is what suits my taste buds  light on the tummy and easy on spices. Please feel free to add/modify ingredients based on your preferences.

1. In a pressure cooker  add 1 slit green chilli along with 5 chopped garlic pods and sauté for a few seconds.
2.Add 1 large onion finely chopped and sauté until golden brown.
3.Add 2 medium-sized tomatoes and let soften.
4.Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell goes off.
5.Now turn your flame low and add spices such as 1 tbspn kashmiri chilli powder  1 tspn turmeric powder  1 tbspn dhaniya-Zeera powder  1 tspn garam masala powder  1.5 tspn chaat masala and salt according to taste.
6.After bhunofying these masalas along with the onion-tomatoes on a low flame  add the Rajma(soaked overnight) and mix well.
7.At this point  also add finely chopped coriander and a dash of lime juice  approx 1 tbspn.
8.Add water just enough to soak the Rajma  not too much not too little.
9.Pressure cook for 4 whistles or until soft but not mushy.
10.Let cool and eventually garnish with more finely chopped coriander.
11.Goes well with both rice and chapati.

main_text: Dal Makhani is made using black lentils (urad dal) and red kidney beans (rajma) that have been soaked overnight. These are mixed with tomato puree a selection of herbs and spices that include garam masala ginger-garlic paste and a large amount of butter. The mix is left to cook overnight on a tandoor so the dal can get a distinct smoky flavor.This dal is served with a generous garnish of fresh butter.Today with modern gadgets like the pressure cooker making dal makhani is not an elaborate time consuming process.HereI served homemade dal Makhani with butter and Parathe I skip using cream to make it little healthy. main_text: Pulses are a subgroup of the legume family but the term “pulse” refers only to the dried seed. Dried beans lentils and peas are the most commonly known and consumed types of pulses.Pulses are abundant in protein as well as vital elements including fiber folate calcium iron and vitamin C. This implies they're great for human health (especially pregnant women) but they're also beneficial for soil health. The capacity of pulses to fix nitrogen increases agriculture production over time.#dal #dalmil #pulses #pulsesindustry #pulsesmanufacturers #pulsesmill #arhar #foodpulses #lentil #lentilrecipe #dalrecipe #kidneybeans #moongdal #blackeyebeans #chanadal #recepies #b2b #b2bmarketplace #b2bfoodstuff #dalimporters #dalmill #rajma #chana #food #healthydal #healthylifestyle #foodindustry
